text:
Hey Kate, please meet Amanda your incredible E-Mentor we've been telling you about :smile:. Feel free to introduce yourselves, say a little bit about what you would like to get out of the mentorship and continue chatting within this channel. :wave:

I will now be leaving the channel, but please direct message myself or penny-prospela if you have any questions. All the best for now! :slightly_smiling_face:

Note: You will not see your match as a "member" in this channel however you can see from the chat history that they have joined/been added :smile:

Hi Amanda!

Thank you for participating in this amazing initiative! I am so excited to learn more from you and have a fruitful cooperation.

I am Kate and I recently relocated to Montreal, Canada from Ukraine. I have so many things to say about my background as I have more than 7 years of professional experience in different industries. I’ll try to be short to describe a general picture of who I am and if you want to know more I’d be glad to share more.

I’ve been managing teams and projects from different industries and countries online and offline for 7 years while working as a Digital Project Manager, Line Producer, Communication Specialist, HR-manager and as an Event-manager. If there is one position that unites all my job experiences, it would be the Project manager, a specialist, who manages people and organizes a fruitful workflow.
In my previous position as a Line Producer at Wow-How Studio, the top video production company named
by Clutch, I had a wide range of responsibilities, managed a few creative teams and 2 coordinators under
my supervision. The projects I worked on were in 2D and 3D animation, VFX production, CG modeling,
concept art creation mainly for advertisingand marketing purposes.
While working in the fast-paced environment on 10-projects simultaneously I was responsible for creating a
schedule for all phases of production and working with Technical Leads to assign digital artists to the work
to successfully deliver 100% of the projects within a deadline driven creative environment. I acted as a
delivery manager and communicated with internal and external international clients like Google and TED-Ed
to manage edits, oversee the execution of client deliveries of all temps and finals. Performing as a problemsolver
and a professional who can stay calm in stressful situations I predicted and resolved a few conflicts
and kept projects on the track.
